	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>I have always been fascinated by the Rogue class and will admit I really know nothing too much, except that when my 60 Chanter wanted a door open he always looked for a Rogue.  So when Luclin was announced I thought what better to sneak around than as an Alleycat.  I Camped Cazic with my Chanter and got my RS 2 months before Luclin release.  I was happy to see that there was a black cat and I think I look splended in all black.<br><br>My question is this.  I did not know that Rogues had archery abilities.  I knew throwing, buy my cat has archery.  Is it worth developing this skill?  Always thought pulling with bow a safe way to pull, but then again a Chanter is usually not a puller. ( although I have done chanter pulls many times)<br><br>Also where is best place to read up on poison making and skill building?  <br>&nbsp;<br>Tommcatt,<br><br>Let's go Cattin'</td></tr>
