<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100801261142325></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100801261142325><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100801261142325>RE: newbie to class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100801261142325#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=33913><span id=Scholar>Dadiella the Charming</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>51 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 10th 2:30 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Use both.  In your lower levels, you probably will do some pulling.  Depending on what kind of zone you are in will determine which to use.  In open outdoor zones like OT and DL, you'll want to use a bow.  In dungeons, thrown weapons are the only way to go because of the tighter spaces. <br><br>Other than that, the ability to crit and hit for Deadly Strikes makes thrown weapons useful for more than pulling.<br><br>Good luck and enjoy your cat burglar :)<br>**Edit:  www.thesafehouse.org  for your skill and poison making questions.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Dec 10 14:36:57 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Dadiella 53rd Level Rogue Drinal<br>Unconquered<br></td></tr>
